        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer146529193" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13219281241854182146">An unappealing mishmash of the BBC TV series, Jane Austen&apos;s novel and a bad Harlequin romance. Mr Darcy seems nearly hysterical at times, coincidences abound, and the intrusion of Colonel Fitzgerald&apos;s older brother muddies everything. In addition, a penniless former lover of Mr Darcy shows up, and although a lady born, is curiously satisfied to be set up as a &quot;couturier&quot; for the ton. Quotes from Ms Austen&apos;s book are tossed in wherever they might fit - apparently in an attempt to legitimize this </span>
  <span id="freeText13219281241854182146" style="display:none">An unappealing mishmash of the BBC TV series, Jane Austen's novel and a bad Harlequin romance. Mr Darcy seems nearly hysterical at times, coincidences abound, and the intrusion of Colonel Fitzgerald's older brother muddies everything. In addition, a penniless former lover of Mr Darcy shows up, and although a lady born, is curiously satisfied to be set up as a "couturier" for the ton. Quotes from Ms Austen's book are tossed in wherever they might fit - apparently in an attempt to legitimize this one as a "real" re-telling of Pride and Prejudice. The one interesting bit was at last Mr Bennett tells Mrs Bennett "No more!". <br /><br />Badly done, Miss Simonsen! Badly done indeed!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13219281241854182146" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

