<div id="review_2220405814" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2220405814" />
    <a title="Debbie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2461325-debbie"><img alt="Debbie" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2220405814?book_show_action=true">Dec 20, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debbie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debbie" href="/user/show/2461325-debbie">Debbie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2220405814" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17325015979087323538">While <i>
  <b>The Perfect Bride for Mr. Darcy</b>
</i> did not cover any new ground, this retelling of <i>Pride and Prejudice</i> was rather inventive. <br/><br/>It was fun that Anne de Bourgh and Georgiana Darcy got in on the plotting game to bring Mr. Darcy and Elizabeth together, not to mention it was nice that Mr. Bennett grew a pair and finally put his wife and unruly younger daughters in their place by setting some ground rules in the Bennett household!<br/><br/>Definitely a fun read for any Jane Austen fan!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


