<div id="review_2376630303" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2376630303" />
    <a title="Michelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7434113-michelle"><img alt="Michelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525027952p2/7434113.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2376630303?book_show_action=true">Apr 29, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle" href="/user/show/7434113-michelle">Michelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2376630303" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12646307008166698119">If you have just one bone in your body that can appreciate good writing do not attempt this book. It is things like this that make me wish Austen were not so very popular to the masses. I read the first chapter before giving it up. It reminded me of some of the 6th grade compositions my friends used to write. Absolutely cringeworthy writing. Don’t. Bother! </span>

          </span>
        </div>


